{"title":"Merida Adds BIG.NINE TR 120mm Hardtail with Geometry Overhauls for Alloy & Carbon","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2024-merida-big-nine-tr-hardtail-alloy-carbon/","date":1690543096000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1600\" height=\"1047\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/MERIDA-BIG-NINE-10K-FRAME-DETAILS.jpg\" alt=\"merida bignine carbon xc hardtail 10k frame detail\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/MERIDA-BIG-NINE-10K-FRAME-DETAILS.jpg 1600w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/MERIDA-BIG-NINE-10K-FRAME-DETAILS-297x194.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/MERIDA-BIG-NINE-10K-FRAME-DETAILS-800x524.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/MERIDA-BIG-NINE-10K-FRAME-DETAILS-120x79.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/MERIDA-BIG-NINE-10K-FRAME-DETAILS-768x503.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/MERIDA-BIG-NINE-10K-FRAME-DETAILS-1536x1005.jpg 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Merida has sharpened up its hardtail XC mountain bike, building upon a platform that has been ridden to many a victory by Mountain Bike Hall of Fame Inductee, Gunn Rita Dahle Flesjå. The 100mm BIG.NINE and the 120mm BIG.NINE TR, both available in aluminum and carbon frame options, are updated with a longer and slacker geometry to deliver a bike with improved descending capabilities in answer to the demands of modern XCO race courses. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The 2024 BIG.NINE doesn’t quite roll into trail riding territory; their <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/merida-big-trail-rolls-onto-29-wheels-to-create-modern-trail-worthy-hardtail/\" target=\"_blank\">BIG.TRAIL</a> hardtail is the tool for that job, but its slacker head angle, lower standover and increased tire clearance come together to create a race-worthy XC bike that offers more comfort, while being more easily controlled by its rider, both up and down the hill.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Pricing runs from £1,400, right up to £9,000.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-carbon-100mm-xc-hardtail-race-bike.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-carbon-100mm-xc-hardtail-race-bike-800x600.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-carbon-100mm-xc-hardtail-race-bike-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-carbon-100mm-xc-hardtail-race-bike-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-carbon-100mm-xc-hardtail-race-bike-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-carbon-100mm-xc-hardtail-race-bike-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-carbon-100mm-xc-hardtail-race-bike-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-carbon-100mm-xc-hardtail-race-bike.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>The 2024 Merida BIG.NINE 10K retails at £9,000, and weighs a claimed 9.3 kg in Size Mid</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>2024 Merida BIG.NINE &amp; BIG.NINE TR</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The new BIG.NINE and BIG.NINE TR hardtails share the same frame, but the latter is fronted by a longer travel fork that slackens off the geometry, reduces reach and lengthens the wheelbase. The frame itself is radically different to the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/pro-bike-check-gunn-rita-dahle-flesjas-old-rose-pink-custom-merida-big-nine-mountain-bike/\" target=\"_blank\">previous incarnation</a>, not least because the last update was as far back as 2018. Key geometry changes are as follows:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>The head angle is 2° slacker, now at 68° (67° on TR)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>The seat tube angle is 1.8° steeper, now at 75.3°</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Reach on the Mid grows by a whopping 31mm, now at 452mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Seat tube length on the Mid is shortened by 34mm for lower standover</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Wheelbase is up by 45mm </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-tr-8000-120mm-fork.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-tr-8000-120mm-fork-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"2024 merida bignine tr 8000 xc hardtail 120mm fork\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-tr-8000-120mm-fork-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-tr-8000-120mm-fork-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-tr-8000-120mm-fork-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-tr-8000-120mm-fork-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-tr-8000-120mm-fork-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-tr-8000-120mm-fork.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>The 2024 Merida BIG.NINE TR 8000 retails at £5,000 and weighs a claimed 10.4 kg in Size Mid</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Short (for XC) stems are paired with 44mm offset forks to prevent front-end handling becoming too lazy. Short and Mid sizes get a 60mm stem, Long and and X-Long get a 70mm stem, and the XX-Long bikes get an 80mm stem.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Not only do the shorter seat tubes allow for longer travel dropper seat posts, but Merida also point out that the significant increase in exposed seat post can give rise to more flex in the post itself, with potential for a little more comfort for long drags of seated pedalling.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-big-nine-geometry.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"479\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-big-nine-geometry-800x479.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-big-nine-geometry-800x479.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-big-nine-geometry-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-big-nine-geometry-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-big-nine-geometry-768x460.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-big-nine-geometry-1536x920.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-big-nine-geometry.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>Merida BIG.NINE CF3 and CF5 carbon frame geometry</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-big-nine-tr-geometry.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"482\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-big-nine-tr-geometry-800x482.jpg\" alt=\"2024 merida big.nine tr geometry\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-big-nine-tr-geometry-800x482.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-big-nine-tr-geometry-297x179.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-big-nine-tr-geometry-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-big-nine-tr-geometry-768x463.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-big-nine-tr-geometry-1536x925.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-big-nine-tr-geometry.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>Merida BIG.NINE CF3 and CF5 carbon frame geometry</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The aluminum frame and the CF3 and CF5 carbon frames seen throughout the range share the same geometry numbers on everything except chainstay length. Indeed, it’s not just weight that sets them apart; the carbon frames also benefit from a size-specific chainstay length that grows somewhat proportionally as reach goes longer.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Importantly, both get a 148mm x 12mm rear end with a SRAM UDH dropout for the hanger-less interface required by the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/sram-gx-eagle-transmission-t-type-review/\" target=\"_blank\">latest SRAM Transmission</a> groups. Thus, this is a 1x specific frame running a 55mm chainline. Tire clearance is boosted to 29″ x 2.4″, there’s a flat-mount for the rear brake, cables are routed internally entering at the headset, and all five frame sizes can accomodate two 750mm water bottles on the downtube.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"2024 merida bignine 600 alloy frame\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>The 2024 Merida BIG.NINE TR 600 retails at £1,400</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>The Aluminum LITE Frame</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The aluminum BIG.NINE is pitched as the more affordable do-it-all hardtail that can just as happily be appropriated as an all-terrain commuting tool, as it can a race bike for the privateer constrained by budget. The frame weighs a claimed 1,920 grams – almost a kilogram heavier than the top-end CF5 frame. It gets a removable kickstand and rear fender mounts, allowing it to adapt to the changing needs of its rider. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Chainstay length is consistent at 433mm across the five frame sizes. That gives a chainstay to reach ratio close to 1 for the Short frame. However, with a reach of 512mm on the XX-Long frame, one doesn’t need a calculator to see how the rider’s position becomes heavily biased toward the rear wheel. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-haedset-cable-routing.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-haedset-cable-routing-800x534.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-haedset-cable-routing-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-haedset-cable-routing-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-haedset-cable-routing-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-haedset-cable-routing-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-haedset-cable-routing-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-haedset-cable-routing-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-haedset-cable-routing.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/v-chainstay-protection.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/v-chainstay-protection-800x534.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/v-chainstay-protection-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/v-chainstay-protection-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/v-chainstay-protection-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/v-chainstay-protection-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/v-chainstay-protection-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/v-chainstay-protection-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/v-chainstay-protection.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-cable-routing.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-cable-routing-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"2024 merida bignine aluminum frame details\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-cable-routing-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-cable-routing-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-cable-routing-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-cable-routing-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-cable-routing-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-cable-routing-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-cable-routing.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-tire-clearance.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-tire-clearance-800x534.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-tire-clearance-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-tire-clearance-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-tire-clearance-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-tire-clearance-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-tire-clearance-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-tire-clearance-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-tire-clearance.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-two-750ml-water-bottles.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-two-750ml-water-bottles-800x534.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-two-750ml-water-bottles-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-two-750ml-water-bottles-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-two-750ml-water-bottles-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-two-750ml-water-bottles-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-two-750ml-water-bottles-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-two-750ml-water-bottles-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-600-alloy-frame-two-750ml-water-bottles.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This has long been the way of things, but a recent trend towards a more proportional approach to geometry is rectifying this to bring the ride feel experienced by short riders and the ride feel experienced by tall riders somewhat closer together. Dependent on your height, you might want to consider the carbon frame options for that improved front-to-rear balance, but be prepared to pay for it.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-carbon-cf5-lightest-frame.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-carbon-cf5-lightest-frame-800x600.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-carbon-cf5-lightest-frame-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-carbon-cf5-lightest-frame-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-carbon-cf5-lightest-frame-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-carbon-cf5-lightest-frame-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-carbon-cf5-lightest-frame-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-carbon-cf5-lightest-frame.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>Only the BIG.NINE 10K gets the lightest, 880g CF5 carbon frame</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>The Carbon CF5 and CF3 Frames</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The BIG.NINE carbon frames are significantly lighter, with the CF3 weighing a claimed 1,100g and the CF5 weighing a claimed 880g. The former is comprised of cheaper carbon fibers that are, presumably, not as strong as the carbon fibers used to produce the CF5 frame. Thus, more of them are required to achieve the same strength and stiffness, hence the additional weight.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-tire-clearance.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-tire-clearance-800x1200.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-tire-clearance-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-tire-clearance-200x300.jpg 200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-tire-clearance-80x120.jpg 80w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-tire-clearance-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-tire-clearance-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-tire-clearance-1365x2048.jpg 1365w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-tire-clearance.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-toptube-graphics.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-toptube-graphics-800x534.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-toptube-graphics-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-toptube-graphics-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-toptube-graphics-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-toptube-graphics-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-toptube-graphics-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-toptube-graphics-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-toptube-graphics.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-accessory-mount.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-accessory-mount-800x534.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-accessory-mount-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-accessory-mount-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-accessory-mount-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-accessory-mount-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-accessory-mount-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-accessory-mount-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-accessory-mount.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-clean-lines.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-clean-lines-800x534.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-clean-lines-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-clean-lines-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-clean-lines-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-clean-lines-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-clean-lines-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-clean-lines-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-bignine-10k-cf5-frame-details-clean-lines.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Both the CF5 and CF3 frames get a size-specific chainstay length, starting at 430mm in the Short, increasing to 442mm in the XX-Long, with 3mm increments between sizes. The improved front-to-rear balance is said to make for an improved climbing experience; with a longer chainstay length it should be easier to keep the front end down on steeper, technical climbs. Similarly, it should be easier to maintain weight through the front tire in flat corners, reducing the risk of wash outs. </p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Other Frame Details</h4>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>No ISCG Mounts; a BB chain guide must be used</li>\n\n\n\n<li>30.9mm seat post diameter</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Threaded BSA BB</li>\n\n\n\n<li>One accessory mount under top tube (CF frames only)</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-smart-mount-for-front-light.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-smart-mount-for-front-light-800x534.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-smart-mount-for-front-light-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-smart-mount-for-front-light-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-smart-mount-for-front-light-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-smart-mount-for-front-light-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-smart-mount-for-front-light-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-smart-mount-for-front-light-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-smart-mount-for-front-light.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-smartmount-for-garmin.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-smartmount-for-garmin-800x534.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-smartmount-for-garmin-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-smartmount-for-garmin-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-smartmount-for-garmin-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-smartmount-for-garmin-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-smartmount-for-garmin-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-smartmount-for-garmin-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-smartmount-for-garmin.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-team-multitool-under-saddle.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-team-multitool-under-saddle-800x534.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-team-multitool-under-saddle-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-team-multitool-under-saddle-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-team-multitool-under-saddle-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-team-multitool-under-saddle-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-team-multitool-under-saddle-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-team-multitool-under-saddle-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/merida-team-multitool-under-saddle.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h4>Bonus Accoutrements</h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Merida go to the extra bother of furnishing their mountain bikes with conveniently stowed tools. Just as we saw on the Merida <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2023-merida-160-140-bikes/\" target=\"_blank\">ONE-FORTY</a> and <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2023-merida-one-sixty-6000-review/\" target=\"_blank\">ONE-SIXTY</a> full suspension bikes, the new BIG.NINE hardtails get a multi-tool stowed underneath the saddle and a 4/6mm allen tool lever on the removable rear axle lever. Actually, this did rattle on our ONE-SIXTY test bike, so we’d hope Merida has fixed that.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The TEAM CC III stem is also equipped with a smart mount for adding a light or cycle computer. There’s also a Trail Mount that can be bolted to the top tube bosses, for secure storage of a spare tube or extra snacks.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Between the carbon and aluminum frame options, and the 100mm BIG.NINE and 120mm BIG.NINE TR, there are no fewer than eight new Merida bikes hitting the market today. Starting with…</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-BIG_NINE_10K_cf3.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"228\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-BIG_NINE_10K_cf3-800x228.jpg\" alt=\"2024 merida big nine 10k xc hardtail cf5 carbon frame\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-BIG_NINE_10K_cf3-800x228.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-BIG_NINE_10K_cf3-297x85.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-BIG_NINE_10K_cf3-120x34.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-BIG_NINE_10K_cf3-768x219.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-BIG_NINE_10K_cf3-1536x438.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-merida-BIG_NINE_10K_cf3.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4>BIG.NINE 10K CF5 – 9.3 kg* –  £9,000</h4>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>100mm RockShox SID SL Ultimate Fork</li>\n\n\n\n<li>SRAM Level Ultimate Stealth 2-Piston Brakes</li>\n\n\n\n<li>SRAM XX Eagle SL Transmission</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Reynolds BLACKLABEL 309/289 XC Carbon Wheels</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Maxxis Rekon Race 29″ x 2.4″, EXO, Tubeless Ready</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-BIG_NINE_TR_8000.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"457\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-BIG_NINE_TR_8000-800x457.jpg\" alt=\"2024 MERIDA BIGNINE TR 8000 CARBON\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-BIG_NINE_TR_8000-800x457.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-BIG_NINE_TR_8000-297x170.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-BIG_NINE_TR_8000-120x69.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-BIG_NINE_TR_8000-768x439.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-BIG_NINE_TR_8000-1536x877.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/2024-BIG_NINE_TR_8000.jpg 1600w\" /></a><figcaption>Also available in Dandelion Green</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h4>BIG.NINE TR 8000 CF3 – 10.4 kg* – £5,000</h4>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>120mm Fox 34 FLOAT SC Performance Elite Fork</li>\n\n\n\n<li>SRAM Level Silver Stealth 2-Piston Brakes</li>\n\n\n\n<li>SRAM GX Eagle Transmission AXS</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Reynolds TR 309/289 XC Wheels</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Maxxis Rekon / Maxxis Rekon Race 29″ x 2.4″ Tires, EXO. Tubeless Ready</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"htt